  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Rinse bell peppers and remove seeds and membranes.",
    "Place them in a bamboo tray lined with parchment paper.",
    "Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with salt, paprika, and black pepper.",
    "Roast in the preheated oven for 20 minutes.",
    "In a small saucepan, combine brown sugar and honey. Heat over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves.",
    "After 20 minutes of roasting, brush the peppers with the sugar glaze.",
    "Continue roasting for another 10 minutes or until peppers are tender.",
    "Remove from oven and let cool for a few minutes.",
    "Crumb goat cheese over the peppers and garnish with parsley, if desired.",
    "Serve warm and enjoy!"
  ],
